✅ Complete End‑to‑End Flow Description (English, Clean & Clear)
Here is the full E2E process in plain English:

1. System generates an order proposal
The backend system creates an automatic order proposal based on stock, forecasts, and time windows.
The store user opens the Ordering App and sees the proposal, including all items and quantities.

2. User logs into the MDE and opens the Ordering App
The user logs into their handheld device (MDE), opens the new Ordering App, and the app loads all open proposals from the system.

3. User reviews articles and adjusts quantities
The proposal displays items and the current stock.
The user can click an article, change the suggested quantity, and the system saves this update.

4. User finalizes the order
After reviewing all positions, the user sends the order.
The app transmits the order to the warehouse, and the order status changes to “Order Sent”.

5. Warehouse receives and processes the order
The warehouse system receives the order and generates a picking task.
Warehouse employees pick the items, and once done, the order is marked “Ready for Delivery”.

6. Delivery leaves the warehouse
When the goods are loaded onto the truck, the system updates the status to “On the Way”.

7. Delivery arrives at the store
The truck arrives at the store.
The user checks the delivery note and verifies that the delivered goods match the order.

8. Final goods receipt is posted in Classic WWS
To finish the process, the store opens the Classic WWS system and performs the official goods receipt posting.
The items are now stored as received, and stock levels update accordingly.



