5. Loss of Network Connection During Ordering
Scenario: Network connection is lost during order editing
Given the user is editing an order proposal
When the network connection is interrupted
Then an offline mode or error is shown
And the user’s entries are not lost
And the user can only send the order after the connection is restored
Summary
If the Wi-Fi or network drops while the user is editing an order, the system must:

Warn the user
Preserve all input
Prevent sending the order until the connection is back

This ensures no data loss and avoids incomplete transmissions.

6. Time Window Conflict When Ordering
Scenario: Order is submitted outside the allowed time window
Given an order proposal includes a binding time window
When the user attempts to send the order after the time window has expired
Then an error message “Time Window Exceeded” appears
And the order is not sent
Summary
Orders must often be submitted within a defined time window (e.g., supplier deadlines).
If the user submits too late, the system blocks the process and informs the user that the deadline has passed.
